5:
Well, what do you think?! Isn't KoiAzu
amazing?!
7:
It really is! Is this series really written
in a world that looks like the Edo
period?!
10: It is! But I've got some bad news...
14:
There aren't any more volumes after
this!
17:
What?! S-so it's on hiatus?! But what
about Princess Inaba?!
20:
Hm... Perhaps if we give the artist our
own Princess Inaho as a
sacrifice—Kidding!
24:
Do middle schools not teach you to
be quiet in the library anymore?
27: Toto? What are you doing here?
29:
Wait, does this mean you're going
back to scho—
34:
Then what's with the book? "The
Fundamentals of Electricity"?
36:
That fox girl wanted to know more
about my body, so she offered me
money to do an examination.
40:
Whoa... What kind of "examination"
are we talking here?
44:
...Anyway, her tests got me curious
too, so I'm looking into it. That's all.
47:
Although the only thing I've figured
out is that I can't figure it out...
50:
Hm? Toto, did something good
happen?
53: Hmph. If you think so, then maybe.
57:
Chika, how do you feel about paying
our brother a visit?
65:
Here it is. We stole back all the parts
from the Starsayers and rebuilt it
ourselves!
69:
It sure is... I'd recognize this eyesore
anywhere.
72:
Nao, you never told me you were
friends with Tohru! That's so cool!
74:
I wouldn't say friends... Although I
suppose my brother does fight his
friends too...
90:
Did you think a little petty theft and
fraud were his only crimes?
93:
Once Shibuya was closed off, he
started mingling with some of the
worst trash out there...
95:
And the best thing to do with trash is
to burn it.
99: Are you... okay with this, Chika?
102:
There was a time when I was little
where Kazu was nice and never hit
me...
103:
As long as I have those memories,
the rest can burn.
112:
When Shibuya was closed off, I
thought this was my only path—my
only option.
114:
Yuto, the Aegis you knew—the one
started by Kazuya—is gone.
117:
You'll have to find your own path
now.
120:
Y-you were the one I looked up to,
Tohru!
122:
I didn't care about Kazuya... YOU
were the one who saved me!
125:
Well, nowadays I'm working for this
squirt's brother.
130:
Again with the stupid nickname? My
name's Nao!
133:
If you really want to work together,
talk to Zekhel in Palpebra or
Takamori in Shibuya. They know
where to reach me.
136: Let's see if you can catch up.
143: Inori, we're done here. Let's go.
150:
You're a lot faster than any taxi I
know. Not as comfortable though.
155:
Well, excuuuse me for not having
seats!
158: Calm down. I'm paying you, aren't I?
169:
So in return, either you take my
money, or you make use of me later
on.
172: The hell are you talking about?!
177: He's saying he wants to be friends!
182:
What part of THAT sounded like he
wants to be friends?! You two read
WAY too much manga!
185: Well, Toto, what did you mean then?
192: Don't try to look cool now!
